When leaves degreen in the process of [[plant senescence]], chlorophyll is converted to a group of colourless [[tetrapyrrole]]s known as '''nonfluorescent chlorophyll catabolites''' (NCC's) with the general structure:

:[[Image:Nonfluorescentchlorophilcatabolites.svg|Nonfluorescent chlorophyll catabolites]]

These compounds have also been identified in several ripening fruits.&lt;ref&gt;
